module com.apocky.loa.systems.substrate_intelligence_stub

// § Labyrinth of Apocalypse · substrate_intelligence STUB
// ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//
// § T11-W17-G · stub-shim for W17-F substrate_intelligence.csl integration
//
// § AUTHORITATIVE-DESIGN-CONTRACT
//   The W17-F sibling agent authors `substrate_intelligence.csl` (the canonical
//   procedural-composition oracle) with public surface :
//     intelligence_query(role, q_kind, q_seed, ctx_ptr, ctx_len) -> u32
//     intelligence_observe(role, obs_kind, obs_seed, ev_ptr, ev_len) -> i32
//     intelligence_compose(role, p_kind, p_seed, params_ptr, params_len,
//                          out_ptr, out_max) -> u32
//
//   This stub mirrors the EXPECTED surface so :
//     1. specialist .csl files can `extern "C"` against canonical names NOW
//     2. when W17-F lands, the host wires real bodies + this stub becomes a
//        passive-import-shim (host-table swap; no .csl-source change)
//     3. tests against specialists run independent of W17-F arrival
//
// § PRIME-DIRECTIVE compliance
//   t∞: ¬ scripted-dialogue · ¬ phrase-pools · ¬ xorshift32-table-lookup
//   t∞: ALL output PROCEDURAL via ω-field + KAN + HDC + causal-seed
//   t∞: Σ-mask gates every emission · default-deny ; cap required to compose
//   t∞: replay-deterministic given (role · seed · observations-history)
//
// § SIBLING-FILES (PER-AGENT-DISPATCH @ T11-W17 wave)
